metadata.title: Mooney M20
aws::graph::propositions: Mooney M20 Aircraft Features and Production History
Wing-mounted air brakes were made available as an option for Mooney M20 in 1985.
Mooney M20 interior was redesigned to improve comfort in 1989.
A 28V electrical system was added to Mooney M20 in 1989.
Electrically-operated cowl flaps were added to Mooney M20 in 1989.
Windows on Mooney M20 were revised with rounded corners in 1989.
Mooney M20 was certified on September 27, 1976.
A total of 1,723 Mooney M20 aircraft were built from 1977 to 1987 and 1989 to 1990.
The 1,723 Mooney M20 aircraft included 201LM, 201SE, and MSE versions.
337 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1977.
380 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1978.
137 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1979.
137 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1980.
176 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1981.
113 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1982.
91 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1983.
82 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1984.
51 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1985.
37 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1986.
53 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1987.
65 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1989.
64 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1990.
M20J 201LM was a "Lean Machine" version of Mooney M20.
M20J 201LM was introduced in 1985.

text:
Wing-mounted air brakes were made available as an option in 1985.  In 1989, the interior was redesigned to improve comfort, a 28V electrical system and electrically-operated cowl flaps were added, and the windows were revised with rounded corners.  Certified September 27, 1976.  A total of 1,723 were built from 1977 to 1987 and 1989 to 1990, including 201LM, 201SE, and MSE versions; 337 (1977), 380 (1978), 137 (1979), 137 (1980), 176 (1981), 113 (1982), 91 (1983), 82 (1984), 51 (1985), 37 (1986), 53 (1987), 65 (1989), and 64 (1990).
M20J 201LM, "Lean Machine" version introduced in 1985.
